      "message": "I agree that relying on `GetSubtree()` here is racy because it observes the current D-Bus state rather than the state that generated InterfacesRemoved.\n\nHowever, I\u0027m not convinced parsing the object path is the best long term solution. D-Bus object paths are identifiers, and their structure should generally be treated as an implementation detail unless the MCTP D-Bus API explicitly guarantees `/networks/{networkId}/endpoints/{eid}` as a stable contract.\n\n\nIf possible, I\u0027d prefer maintaining a mapping from `object_path` to `{networkId, EID}` (or relying on cached properties/interfaces populated from InterfacesAdded) and using the object path from InterfacesRemoved as the lookup key. That avoids both the race condition and coupling the consumer to the path layout.",
